The National Emergency Management Agency(NEMA) has said one person died in a fire incident at Kalari Muna Elbadawy Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) camp, Maiduguri while 17 others were injured. Principal Information Officer NEMA North-East, Abdulkadir Ibrahim, who disclosed this to NAN said about 100 shelters were destroyed, while dozens of households in the camps were displaced as a result of the incident. He said the fire which started from a cooking fire in one of the IDP tents was brought under control by the personnel of the State Fire Service. 2023: Let’s Give Tinubu Opportunity To Fix Nigeria,… Group Warns Detractors From Distracting Akinwumi, Lokoja Varsity… Ibrahim explained that the injured victims had been administered first aid. He added that a combined team of the NEMA and the State Emergency Management Agency (SEMA) were on ground to assess the extent of destruction in the camp.